column10: Driver pulled perpendicularly into the bike lane, blocking it and the entire travel lane with her massive SUV.  She sat there stopped for a moment, so I cautiously tried to go around her, at which point she floored it and nearly hit me.  I had on multiple bike lights and a neon jacket, so she should have seen me.  I legitimately thought for a moment she was actively trying to hit me.
column21: If the bike lane were protected with a concrete curb or similar barrier, she would not have been able to swing dangerous into it and block the lane the way she did.  She also would have had a much harder time nearly killing me.
